Employment in Mauritian businesses
that have at least 10 people increased to 302,215 in the 12
months through March from a year earlier, the nationâ€™s
statistics office said.  Employment rose from 298,454 as of March 2009, the Port
Louis-based Central Statistics Office said in a statement
published on its website today.  The health and social-work industry added the most jobs,
with 2,225 appointments. Manufacturing shed 2,418 positions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
